<h1 style="color:blue">Authority</h1>
    <asp:Label runat="server" Font-Bold="true" ForeColor="Red"> Who is the Mayor :</asp:Label><br /><br />

    <div runat="server" style="width:50% ;">
   He is the first official in the municipality and has great powers in terms
   of implementing projects, hiring and purchasing the necessary cars for him, municipal employees, heavy equipment and 
  construction of municipal buildings. He can delegate some of his powers to his deputy or assistant
</div>
    <p style="color:red"> Role of the Mayor</p>
    <p style="width:50%">
       <b>For the technical department</b>, which is responsible for the planning of cities, 
        buildings and government projects and to grant the necessary licenses for this.
    </p>
    <p style="width:50%"> 
    <b>Department of Environmental Health</b> and is usually headed by a veterinarian or 
    health inspector task of this section grant health to open shops and private.
    And follow up the cleanliness of the city and control markets and shops that have to do with public
    health and the liberalization of violations of the violators of shop owners.
    </p>
    <p style="width:50%"> 
        <b>Land and Infringement Control Section</b>is a department responsible for controlling government and white land
        and preventing infringements or building therein without a title deed or building permit from the municipality.
    </p>
    <p style="width:50%"><b>The Finance Department</b> is responsible for expenses and revenues from the budget allocated
        to the municipality and provides the necessary equipment for other sections of the municipality.</p>
    <p style="width:50%">
          <b>The Investment Department</b> is a division responsible for municipal investments, land grants, 
        schemes and land allocation to other government agencies and others.

    </p>
    <p style="width:50%"> 
     <b>The Personnel Section</b> is responsible for all employees in terms of their salaries, 
        leave and rights. The position of Director of Personnel is usually the Assistant to the Mayor.
 </p>
